item.content:encoded:
The E-MTB Heckler has become an established part of the portfolio of the Californian high-end brand Santa Cruz. The dream e-mountain bike is still powered by Shimano’s EP-8 motor, but the capacity of the elegantly in the premium carbon frame integrated battery has grown by a massive 43% to 720 Wh – you’ve never been able to ride your favorite trail so often! The Mullet variant MX (Mixed) comes in sizes M to XXL at the front with 29″ and at the rear with 27.5″ wheels, size S is equipped with 27.5″ wheels at the front and rear.
  • Functional Storage Featuring An Easy Side-Access Storage Space
  • 7″ TFT Instrumentation with Smartphone Connectivity & Multiple Display Modes
  • LED Accent Lights and Rearview Camera
  • Kawasaki Corner Management Function (KCMF)
  • Kawasaki TRaction Control (KTRC)

item.title: Product 2
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Danny MacAskill just doesn’t stop talking about ebikes. He’s infatuated with them. In fact, the only time he’s not chewing someone’s ear off about how good they are is when he’s riding them. And when he’s riding an ebike he rides and rides and rides. This is partly why we’ve made the newest Heckler able to go further, higher, faster and be funner. The latest generation of the Heckler has a larger interchangeable battery (720wh up from 504wh), which allows riders to expand their own trail map – accessing previously unreachable trails, unlocking less-used trails and cramming more into less time.
  • NEW Auto Hi-Beam (AHB) sensor
  • Tire Pressure Monitoring System (TPMS)
  • Vehicle Hold Assist (VHA)
  • Kawasaki’s Intelligent Proximity Activation
  • USB-style power outlet

Zero is Mondraker’s proprietary most efficient, best performing and super capable suspension system. Zero is a dual link design with the shock floating between the two suspension links and compressed from both ends. This makes the rear suspension extremely sensitive to small bumps and big hit capable.

item.title: Product 5
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Bianchi’s Gravel bikes ideally combine the emotional closeness to nature with the exciting Bianchi racing DNA. The Bianchi Arcadex GRX 810 1x11sp is the perfect bike for experienced riders who love to ride fast and in control, whatever the terrain. The carbon frame is incredibly responsive, so the Arcadex is ready to perform as soon as you pedal- whether you’re exploring or indulging your competitive spirit. Combine off-road capability with the speed and aesthetics you love on your road bike, and you get the Arcadex. With room for 700×42 or 650×47 tires, it’s for those who want to go faster on gravel.

An amazingly capable, versatile gravel road bike. Built for chasing horizons, exploring routes less travelled or accelerating your commute. Straightforward, reliable and a whole hell of a lotta fun, the Cannondale Topstone Alloy is a gravel bike crafted for those with a taste for adventure – and value. Roll light and free, or load it up for a long haul, Topstone’s comfortable ride, confident handling and up-for-anything capability make it the perfect partner on any road, anywhere.
  • Lightweight SmartForm C2 aluminum frame
  • Topstone Carbon Fork
  • OutFront steering geometry
  • 700×45 mm & 27.5 x 2.1” tire clearance
  • Simple and easy internal cable routing
  • Ready for dropper seatpost

Focus uses only those drives and batteries that enable them to create a modern, agile and aggressive geometry for the JAM² thanks to their compact construction. This means that you will have just as much fun out on the trail as with the non-electric JAM. All bikes have been approved for a system weight of 150 kg without any compromise in regards to intended use. Not only does this prove the reliability of our bikes, it also provides heavier riders to discover their happy place safely.

item.title: Product 8

item.content:encoded:
Engineered with AeroSystem Shaping technology and Advanced-grade composite material, the all-new Propel Advanced combines proven aero performance and one of the lightest framesets in its category. New cable routing through the stem and head tube makes it quick and easy to adjust and dial in rider positioning. The lightweight, easily adjustable Vector composite seatpost further minimizes drag. If you value style at speed or want to have fun feeling fast, then mixed wheels (29” up front, 27.5” out back) are the right choice.

The FOCUS JAM² is all-out fun on the trail. Supported by the compact Shimano EP8 e-drive with 720 Wh, you can ride more trails at the same time. With a perfectly tuned 150 mm F.O.L.D. chassis, 29“ wheels and a super agile geometry the JAM² is more playful than ever before. You will ride more mountains, more trails and gather more experiences.
Notwithstanding the foregoing, frames purchased prior to May 1, 2015 are covered under the previously-existing warranty for five years from the original date of purchase. item.title: Product 10
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
We at Lapierre use four distinct fibre types, each with its own characteristics. Our engineers can use these different fibres to adapt the stiffness, flex and strength needed for the parts of the frame in question. High-strength fibre is what you will need for shock absorption and comfort: seatpost, chainstays, seatstays or even the whole frame. Very high-modulus, meanwhile, will have unyielding stiffness and efficiency.
Recommended Frame Size
  • S: 150 – 170 cm
  • M: 168 – 178 cm
  • L: 176 – 186 cm
  • XL: >184 cm
Agile Ride Geometry delivers confidence-inspiring handling, as you’d expect. There’s an Easy Entry frame option, and a new S frame with 27.5in wheels, so everyone can find their ideal Reaction Hybrid. And, with internally routed cables including a stealth dropper post upgrade option, we’ve reduced the need for maintenance so that you can just enjoy the ride.
